==English==

===Alternative Spelling===
*[[caldron]]

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} from {{OF.}} [[caudron]], based on {{L.}} [[calidarium]]/[[caldarium]] meaning ''cooking-pot'', from [[calidus]] meaning ''hot''.

===Pronunciation===
* [[w:IPA_chart_for_English|IPA]]: /kɔldrən/
* [[w:SAMPA/English|SAMPA]]: /koldr@n/.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A large bowl-shaped pot used for boiling over an open flame.
{{seeCites}}

